*20* 
 grammar: The correct verb tense to use in this sentence is "avaient eu" (imparfait) instead of "étaient réussis" (passé composé). 

The teacher's comment is correct. The verb "avoir" (to have) in the imparfait tense should be used to describe a past possession or experience. In this case, the correct form is "avaient eu" (imparfait of avoir) instead of "étaient réussis" (passé composé of être réussi). 

A corrected version of the sentence would be: "Les autres marins dans la zone avaient eu Internet par satellite."  
 
 
*21* 
 """Grammar: Incorrect use of the verb être (to be) in the past tense."""

